1. Filter by Specific Field Matching (Exact Text)
If you want to look inside the metadata object for a specific value matching exactly (e.g., finding products in a specific category or by a specific brand).

JSON
{
  "query": "wireless headphones",
  "filters": {
    "category": {
      "eq": "Electronics"
    },
    "brand": "Sony"
  }
}
2. Numeric Range Filtering (Prices, Inventory, Dates)
Because your FilterBuilder safely converts gt, gte, lt, and lte into ::numeric operations for custom metadata fields, you can execute complex numeric range matches.

JSON
{
  "query": "mechanical keyboard",
  "filters": {
    "price": {
      "lte": 150
    },
    "stock_count": {
      "gt": 0
    }
  }
}
3. Bounded Range Filtering (between)
This passes exactly two arguments into an array block to isolate variables falling inside a predefined scale.

JSON
{
  "query": "running shoes",
  "filters": {
    "size": {
      "between": [8, 11]
    }
  }
}
4. Multi-Value Inclusions (in / notIn)
This lets you look across multiple specific variants simultaneously. It works perfectly on root columns (like source_table) or metadata values (like status codes).

JSON
{
  "query": "billing error log",
  "filters": {
    "source_table": {
      "in": ["stripe_webhooks", "customer_invoices"]
    },
    "status": {
      "notIn": ["resolved", "archived"]
    }
  }
}
5. String Text Traversal (contains, startsWith, endsWith)
Your code converts these keywords into PostgreSQL case-insensitive pattern matching (ILIKE). Great for partial serial numbers, titles, or tags.

JSON
{
  "query": "onboarding issues",
  "filters": {
    "title": {
      "contains": "tutorial"
    },
    "serial_code": {
      "startsWith": "ERR_"
    },
    "file_extension": {
      "endsWith": "pdf"
    }
  }
}
6. Combined Complex Matrix (Root + Metadata Filter)
You can mix everything together. The engine will isolate the query within specific tables, check a custom field's numeric threshold, and match on text strings simultaneously.

JSON
{
  "query": "security patch update",
  "filters": {
    "source_table": "system_logs",
    "created_at": {
      "gte": "2026-01-01"
    },
    "severity_score": {
      "gt": 7.5
    },
    "component_name": {
      "contains": "auth-service"
    }
  }
}












